SIMPLE: overtime
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overtime
<hw>O"ver*time`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Time
beyond, or in excess of, a limit; esp., extra working time.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Sports)</fld> <def>An extra period of time provided
to play a game, beyond the end of the normal period allowed for the
game, for the purpose of resolving a tie score; <as>as, the team won in
<ex>overtime</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>sudden death overtime</b></col> <cd>an overtime{2} in
which the first team to score wins the game; -- contrasted with normal
overtime{2}, which is a fixed period of time during which either team
may score as often as they can.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overtire</ent>⟦br⟧
